### The typeof Operator

TypeScript's `typeof` operator (when used in a type context) captures the type of a value or variable.

### Type Context typeof

```typescript
const user = {
  name: "Alice",
  age: 30
};

type UserType = typeof user;
// { name: string; age: number }

const other: UserType = {
  name: "Bob",
  age: 25
};
```

### Runtime typeof vs Type typeof

| Context | Behavior |
|---------|----------|
| JavaScript runtime | Returns `"string"`, `"number"`, etc. |
| TypeScript type context | Captures the static type of a value |

```typescript
// Runtime typeof
console.log(typeof "hello"); // "string"

// Type context typeof
type T = typeof "hello"; // "hello" (literal)
```

### typeof with Class

```typescript
class Point {
  constructor(public x: number, public y: number) {}
}

type PointConstructor = typeof Point;
// typeof Point is the constructor function type
// new (x: number, y: number) => Point
```

### typeof with Arrays

```typescript
const fruits = ["apple", "banana", "cherry"] as const;
type Fruit = (typeof fruits)[number];
// "apple" | "banana" | "cherry"
```

### Keyof with typeof

```typescript
const config = {
  host: "localhost",
  port: 3000,
  secure: true
} as const;

type ConfigKeys = keyof typeof config;
// "host" | "port" | "secure"

type ConfigValues = (typeof config)[keyof typeof config];
// "localhost" | 3000 | true
```

> **Key Point:** In type context, `typeof` extracts the type of a value, enabling type reuse from runtime code.

codeExample:
// Extract type from a value
const settings = {
  theme: "dark",
  fontSize: 14,
  notifications: true
};

type Settings = typeof settings;
// { theme: string; fontSize: number; notifications: boolean }

// Extract literal types with as const
const Colors = ["red", "green", "blue"] as const;
type ColorName = (typeof Colors)[number];

// Use with keyof
type SettingKey = keyof typeof settings;

function getSetting(key: SettingKey): typeof settings[SettingKey] {
  return settings[key];
}
